node.text: Marriage equality has been the law of the land for nearly six years, but inequality and violence toward the LGBTQ+ community still persists in far too many parts of our society. That must change – immediately. To celebrate and mark Pride Month, I spoke with my constituent and the first openly gay Hollywood stuntman, Shawn Balentine (@shawnbalentine_stunts) about his incredible life story and the urgent need to pass the Equality Act. The Equality Act will create consistent federal protections barring discrimination in housing, employment, public spaces, and more for LGBTQ+ individuals, so that no one faces discrimination anywhere in the U.S. simply because of who they love or how they identify. The Senate must take up and pass this critical legislation – because because no one is truly free until all are free.

node.title: It's Time to Pass the Equality Act

node.text:
The House Intelligence Committee held our annual open World Wide Threats hearing today, with the heads of our nation’s intelligence agencies — DNI, CIA, FBI, NSA and Pentagon – to discuss emerging threats facing our nation and around the world, and how we can confront them.
 
Here’s what you need to know:

1️⃣ China is our biggest competitor in every sphere, especially in the cyber space, with their malign activities including theft of intellectual property, government information, and private data.

2️⃣ Russia poses a continuing threat, through their election interference, amassing troops on the Ukraine border, poisoning dissidents like Alexei Navalny, and cyber attacks.

3️⃣ We need to focus on the so-called ‘soft threats,’ too, like climate change and pandemic disease, which can kill you just as dead as a ‘hard threat.’

Calling all Angelenos: Have you made a plan to vote? If not, join me in making a plan to vote right now. It’ll only take a few minutes.

And if you’re not registered to vote, visit https://registertovote.ca.gov/ today to get registered – the deadline in California is this Monday, October 19! You can also register on Election Day by casting a provisional ballot, but registering only takes a few minutes, so why not get it done today? 

The election is just a few weeks away. This may be the most important election of our lifetimes. The stakes could not be higher. So we need to make sure every voice is counted. Vote!

(Not from Los Angeles? You need to make a plan to vote, too! Visit vote.org to learn about deadlines and processes in your state.)

node.text: Part of the magic of Los Angeles is the natural beauty and majestic wildlife right in our backyard. And it’s up to all of us to protect it. For decades, I’ve been working to preserve the Rim of the Valley corridor – 200,000 acres of open space around the LA County basin – and my friends at @npcapics just released this wonderful virtual tour that highlights just what makes this area so special. Let’s do all we can to protect this natural beauty, not just for us, but for generations to come.

node.text: I’ve heard from hundreds of constituents and people across the country who are “mixed earners” – freelancers, contract workers, and those in the gig economy who earn income from a mix of sources – and have been unable to receive the unemployment benefits they deserve and need. That’s why I introduced the Mixed Earner Pandemic Unemployment Assistance Act to help fix the problem and ensure that no one is left behind in our response to the coronavirus economic crisis. I want to share just a few of their stories.

node.text: Black Lives Matter.‬ ‪The murder of George Floyd once again displays the harsh reality of racial bias and police brutality that black Americans confront in our country.‬ ‪As millions take to the steets to demand justice, I had some reflections I wanted to share.

node.accessibility_caption:
Investigating January 6 is a sober endeavor. One demanding good faith participation from both parties. 

Time after time, McCarthy has shown he is not up to that task. 

But we cannot allow him to derail our important work or appoint others who will.

We will uncover the truth.

Photo by Adam Schiff in California State Capitol. May be an image of 1 person, child and text that says '"For any child to go hungry is an absolute travesty- and an abject policy failure." ADAM I SCHIFF REPRESENTING CALIFORNIA'S 28TH DISTRICT'.

node.text: No child should ever have to wonder when or where their next meal will come from – yet, for too long, food insecurity has been the bitter reality for millions of kids in California. For any child to go hungry is an absolute travesty – and an abject policy failure. But we are not powerless to end child hunger. Bipartisan lawmakers in California just launched the nation’s largest universal free lunch program, which will ensure that no child goes through school hungry. More states should follow suit – and soon. Because the health and wellbeing of our children can’t wait.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schiff in La Canada Flintridge, California with @collin_morikawa. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text: At just 24 years old, @collin_morikawa has propelled himself to the very top of the professional golfing world – making history as the first man to win both the PGA Championship and the Open during tournament debuts. Collin, a La Cañada High School alum, makes all of us back home in Los Angeles incredibly proud. Congratulations, Collin!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schiff in Los Angeles, California. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text: People often ask me what the hardest part of my job is. But that’s not nearly as important as the best part of my job, the part that makes it all worth it: meeting incredible Angelenos who call California’s 28th Congressional District home.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schiff in United States House of Representatives. May be a black-and-white image of 1 person.

node.text: A year ago, we lost one of our greatest leaders in Congress, an American hero, and a dear friend. While we feel his absence, his spirit will never leave us. It inspires us to keep making good trouble. And fighting to protect the vote. We miss you, John.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schiff in Los Angeles, California. May be an image of 2 people, child, tree and text.

node.text: Calling all coders, developers, entrepreneurs, and big thinkers! It’s that time of the year again: the Congressional App Challenge is underway! Each year, the House of Representatives hosts a competition for students across the country to develop an app that helps improve and better the communities we all share. From now until November 1, middle and high school students living in the 28th Congressional District can submit their app at CongressionalAppChallenge.us. You can also find more information on rules and eligibility there, too. I can’t wait to see what our students come up with this year!

The pandemic was hard on us all, but perhaps no one made more sacrifices than students and families.

We're on our way to getting students back in classrooms— back with friends, back with teachers, and back on track to succeed.

Thrilled to have @seccardona in Los Angeles today.
